"GIT and GitHub"
Commands for Git
------------———— -->Git configuration
Run git config –global user.name "[name]" to use it.  
git config –global user.email "[email address]" is how it is used.  
This command configures your commits to use the specified author name and email address, accordingly.
-->git init Use: git init [name of repository]
One uses this command to launch a fresh repository.
-->git add git add [file] is the usage  
A file is appended to the staging area by this command.
-->git commit
To use, type git commit -m "[Enter the commit message]".  
This command creates a permanent snapshot or record of the file in the version history.

Utilization of git status  
All of the files that need to be committed are listed by this command.
